What subject did you like at school

I really enjoyed studying English when I was a student. It played a crucial role in improving my communication skills and broaden my perspective.
In addition, it was a refreshing break from more demanding subjects like science. What I liked most was that the lessons were quite interactive compared to other classes, which made them more engaging and enjoyable.

Is education important to you
Yes, definitely. I believe education plays a vital role in shaping both personal development and career success. It not only provides essential knowledge but also helps individuals develop critical skills like problem-solving, analytic thinking, and effective communication.

Did you enjoy your school life
Overall, yes. When I was a student, I was surrounded by dedicated teachers and supportive classmates who were always willing to lend a hand whenever I faced challenges.
Although the academic pressure was quite high, as I had to complete a heavy workload within limited time, I still found my school life enjoyable and rewarding.

